# maskline runs fully offline with no .env at all: the LLM routing chain falls
# through to a deterministic classifier, so every number reproduces with zero
# keys and zero cost. Set any of these to route free-text PHI classification +
# the executive summary to a real model. NEVER commit real keys; on a public
# host leave them unset (offline).

# --- Routing mode -----------------------------------------------------------
# auto (default) walks the full chain; or pin a tier: paid | local | free | offline
# LLM_MODE=auto

# --- Paid providers (tried first in auto) -----------------------------------
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Local Ollama (autodetected via /api/tags; cost $0) ---------------------
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b

# --- Free providers (OpenRouter free-tier models) ---------------------------
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-key-here
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=google/gemma-4-31b-it:free

# --- Warehouse connector ----------------------------------------------------
# Local demo uses an in-memory DuckDB with Snowflake-compatible SQL. In prod,
# point the connector at a real Snowflake account; the generated MASKING POLICY /
# ROW ACCESS POLICY DDL + Terraform target the Snowflake provider.
# MASKLINE_WAREHOUSE=duckdb   # duckdb (default) | snowflake
